claim.claim-text:
An assembly (22) for forming an inductive telemetry connection comprising:
a first side connector (26) including:
a first protective housing (32) including a first end face (36);
a first inductor (46) contained within the first protective housing (32) and adjacent to the first end face (36), the first inductor (46) having a first axis (A1);
a first physical connector element (34); and
a second side connector (28) including:
a second protective housing (40) including a second end face (44);
a second inductor (58) contained within the second protective housing (40) and adjacent to the second end face (44), the second inductor (58) having a second axis (A2); and
a second physical connector element (42) configured to engage with the first physical connector element (34) such that the first end face (36) the second end face (44) are adjacent, and physically connect the first side connector (26) to the second side connector (28) such that the first axis (A1) and the second axis (A2) are generally aligned with each other;
wherein the first inductor (46) and the second inductor (58) form an inductive telemetry connection between the first side connector (26) and the second side connector (28).

A connector assembly comprising:
a first side connector (26) including:
a first protective housing (32) including a first end face (36);
a first inductor (46) contained within the first protective housing (32) and adjacent to the first end face (36), the first inductor (46) having a first axis (A1);
a first physical connector element (34); and
a second side connector (28) including:
a second protective housing (40) including a second end face (44);
a second inductor (58) contained within the second protective housing (40) and adjacent to the second end face (44), the second inductor (58) having a second axis (A2); and
a second physical connector element (42) engaged with the first physical connector element (34), and physically connecting the first side connector (26) to the second side connector (28) such that the first end face (36) and the second end face (44) are adjacent, the first axis (A1) and the second axis (A2) are generally aligned with each other, the first inductor (46) and the second inductor (58) are axially spaced apart;
wherein the first inductor (46) and the second inductor (58) form an inductive telemetry connection between the first side connector (26) and the second side connector (28).

A transducer assembly (18) including:
a sensing element (80);
sensor wiring or interconnect (82) connected to the sensing element (80); and
a sensor housing (76) containing the sensing element (80), the sensor housing (76) including an opening through which an electrical connection to the sensor wiring (82) passes;
an electrical cable (24) for electrically connecting to a measurement or control system; and
the assembly or connector assembly (22) according to any preceding claim, wherein the first wire coil (50) is electrically connected to the sensor wiring (82), the first protective housing (32) is sealed over the opening in the sensor housing (76) such that the first side connector (26) projects from the sensor housing (76), and the sensor housing (76) and the first protective housing (26) together form a hermetically sealed enclosure; and wherein the second wire coil (62) is electrically connected to an end of the electrical cable (24), and the second side connector (28) is located at the end of the electrical cable (24).
